Error: Error: "Java Heap Space Error" On Pterodactyl Panel Minecraft Server.

Solution: 1. Log in to your Pterodactyl panel and go to the "File Manager" section.

2. Locate the server.properties file in the "root" directory, and click on "Edit."

3. Scroll down to the "Java arguments" section and find the "-Xmx" flag. This flag defines the amount of memory allocated to the Minecraft server.

